[[File:Debosnys-Cryptogram-1.png|thumb|A self-portrait of Debosnys with a pictogram.]]

'''Henry Debosnys''' (born 1836 in [[Lisbon]], [[Portugal]]; died April 28, 1883 in [[Essex County, New York|Essex County]], [[New York (state)|New York]]) was hanged for murder of his third wife, Elizabeth Wells.<ref>[http://www.lakeplacidnews.com/page/content.detail/id/502314/Mysterious-wife-killer-once-again-a-topic.html Eric Voornis: ''Mysterious wife killer once again a topic:'' 2. April 2010]</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://books.google.de/books?id=xcd1OqTaPcYC&pg=PA78&lpg=PA78&dq=Henry+Debosnys+portugal&source=bl&ots=kosHKBwlXw&sig=kBC93c4PDsvH3xMFJMz3pDslsgs&hl=de&sa=X&ved=0CDMQ6AEwAmoVChMIuoDoseaFyQIV4qZyCh1TWgTF#v=onepage&q=Henry+Debosnys+portugal&f=false|title=The Big Book of New York Ghost Stories|first=Cheri|last=Revai|date=20 February 2009|publisher=Stackpole Books|via=Google Books}}</ref> His skull is on display at the Adirondack History Center Museum in [[Elizabethtown, New York]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://strangeremains.com/2014/04/13/the-cranium-of-the-last-man-hanged-in-essex-county-ny/|title=The cranium of the last man hanged in Essex County, NY|date=14 April 2014|publisher=}}</ref>

Debosnys left [[cipher|enciphered]] documents, that have never been decrypted, using a [[Cryptography|cryptographic]] script (or scripts) and/or [[pictograms]].

