'''Kir-Balar''' (also known as Kir, Kirr) is an [[Afro-Asiatic languages|Afro-Asiatic]] language spoken in Kir Bengbet and Kir Bajang’le villages, [[Bauchi|Bauchi LGA]] [[Bauchi State]], [[Nigeria]].<ref name=e18/>

