{{Infobox language |name=Mehináku |states=[[Brazil]] |region=[[Mato Grosso]] |ethnicity=[[Mehinako people|Mehinako]] |speakers=230 |date=2006 |ref=e18 |familycolor=American |fam1=[[Maipurean languages|Arawakan]] |fam2=Southern ? |fam3=[[Paresi–Waura languages|Paresí–Xingu]] |fam4=Waurá |fam5=Waura–Mehináku |iso3=mmh |glotto=mehi1240 |glottorefname=Mehináku |linglist=qdv |lingname=Waura–Mehináku }}
'''Mehináku''' (Meinaku) is an [[Arawakan languages|Arawakan language]] spoken by the [[Mehinaku]] people of [[Brazil]]. One dialect, Waurá-kumá, is "somewhat [[mutually intelligible|intelligible]]" with [[Waurá language|Waurá]] due to influence from this language.<ref name=e18/>
