'''Tanga people''' are a tribe of a [[Papua New Guinea]] that live in the [[Tanga Islands]] and [[Feni Islands]] of [[Tanir Rural LLG]] and three villages (Sena,Muliama and Warangansau) in the [[Matalai Rural LLG]] of [[Namatanai District]] of [[New Ireland Province]]. The people are closely related to the [[Tolai people]] and Sursurunga people of New Ireland and they speak the [[Tangga language]] which has since been split into three separate languages which are now being spoken by the Tangans and they are [[Niwer Mil language]], [[Warwar Feni language]] and [[Fanamaket language]]. Their population according to the 2011 Papua New Guinea Census Report is 9,033 people. Tubuan, Sokapana and Ingiet are the secret societies practised by the Tanga people. F.L.S. Bell has a collection on Tanga Island in the [[University of Sydney]] Library in Australia.<ref>https://library.sydney.edu.au/collections/rare-books/downloads/bell.pdf</ref>
